2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 203
BY REPRESENTATIVE BAMBURG
CONDOLENCES: Expresses the condolences of the House of Representatives to the
families of the children whose lives were taken in the mass shooting in Shreveport
and affirms its stance against domestic violence
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the condolences of the House of Representatives to the families of the children
3 whose lives were taken in the mass shooting in Shreveport and to affirm its stance
4 against domestic violence.
5 WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
6 Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the tragic mass shooting in
7 Shreveport, Louisiana, that claimed the lives of eight children on April 19, 2026; and
8 WHEREAS, the state of Louisiana and Bossier Parish stand firmly against domestic
9 violence and offer prayers and support to the families of Mar'Kaydon Pugh, Kayla Pugh,
10 Layla Pugh, Jayla Elkins, Shayla Elkins, Sariahh Snow, Khedarrion Snow, and Braylon
11 Snow.
12 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
13 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby express heartfelt condolences to the families of the
14 children whose lives were taken in the mass shooting in Shreveport and does hereby affirm
15 its stance against domestic violence.
